HEADWORD: Tailboard
<hw>Tail"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The board at the
rear end of a cart or wagon, which can be removed or let down, for
convenience in loading or unloading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

